comment.author: 24595374@N05
comment._content:
Yea, old '34, remember it like it was yesterday. The Great Depression lingered with a devastating impact on the dreams and hopes of generations, especially those of us in the Dust Bowl. The dog in the photo above reminds me so much of my neighbor who lost his farm in late '30. I called him Bull because everyone else did too. He lost his bull in '30; of course, I referring to his livestock, not his disposition, although he did seem full of something when he recounted his stories about his fishing. Last heard, old Bull entered politics, which, I guess, would have been a smooth transition for someone with his penchant for bull; here, of course, I'm not referring to livestock. Yea, old Bull, in '34 or maybe it was '36. Can't really remember; yea, Bull had that kind of an effect on me too.

Anyway, I enjoyed visiting here, admiring your great talent. Gotta go.
